<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="593" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Wang &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" box="[552,720,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Neopheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudofasciata">
<emphasis box="[552,720,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">pseudofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the other specific name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moore)" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1171,1361,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Pheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1171,1260,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">fasciata</emphasis>
(Moore)
</taxonomicName>
due to the resemblance of the present new species in external characters to the species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1044,1166,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Pheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1044,1166,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">N. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="593" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Remarks.</emphasis>
Morphologically, the new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[885,1005,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Pheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[885,1005,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">N. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished in forewing pattern and genitalia characters of both sexes. Molecularly (
<figureCitation box="[837,921,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1475,1499]" captionTargetBox="[151,1422,681,1442]" captionTargetId="figure-234@4.[151,1436,669,1452]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 15. Maximum Likelihood (ML) tree for the 2 species of Neopheosia based on COI gene." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911634/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), the lineage of the new species has a strong support (bootstrap=100) and the genetic distance between the new species and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1056,1180,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Pheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[1056,1180,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">N. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reached from 6.9% to 7.4%; the genetic distance between some genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[723,869,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="590" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dicranurinae">Dicranurinae</taxonomicName>
is more than 10%. Furthermore, the two species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Wang &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Neopheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudofasciata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">N. pseudofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[371,491,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Pheosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[371,491,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">N. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distributed sympatrically. Hence, the validity of the new species is well supported by morphological, molecular and geographic evidence. For the convenience of identification, a key to 
<taxonomicName pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Neopheosia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
is given below:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
